                      <td valign="top" height="100%"><font face="Verdana" size="2" color="white"><span class="spnMessageText" id="msg"> Hi,<br /><br />Theres more danger here than you might suspect.<br /><br />Just cause you /hold a pet, dont mean you make him blind. If shit starts hitting him, hes going to add that shit to his aggro list. AE makers too...hes just not going to do shit about it, until....<br /><br />So... you hold yer pet. An AE hits him. He adds AE fucker to his list. You tell him to attack random_other_mob. Guess whathe does? he goes after the AEer. Oopps..<br /><br />Preface every command with /pet back off to clear his aggro list and you cna avoid some of the problems this sets up. And as others suggested, the only reasonable way to /pet hold something is to /pet hold /pet back off in  that order... Hold him, and clear his list. If you suspect he got hit again, mash yer hold/clear button again...<br /><br />Terial "Used to think pet hold was broken too" Mierdrath<br /><br /></span id="msg"></font><br><br></td>
